This file tracks the status of releases in the 1.4.x line.

See "Stabilizing and maintaining releases" in trunk/www/hacking.html for
details on how release lines and voting work, what kinds of bugs can
delay a release, etc.

Status of 1.4.0:
================

Candidate changes:

  * r19605, r19565, r19564, r19533, r19531
    Backport mod_dontdothat.
    Justification:
      Low impact (just contrib), people want the abilities it gives them.
    Votes:
      +1: rooneg, lundblad

  * r19620
    Fix hang in ra_svn when locking unreadable file.
    Justification:
      Server protocol error.
    Votes:
      +1: lundblad, dlr

  * r19636
    Fix up $INSTALL after AC_PROG_INSTALL.
    Justification:
      Avoid build breakage on Solaris with VPATH build.
    Votes:
      +1: maxb, lundblad

  * r19638
    Fix bug: Use of log with limit against a pre-1.3.x svnserve which does not
    support limit renders the RA session unusable for future commands.
    Votes:
      +1: maxb

  * r19656
    Eliminate dead code in notification fflushing.
    Justification:
      Regression: no fflush after each period in post-commit txdelta
      transmission.
    Votes:
      +1: lundblad, dlr

  * r19527 (testcase), r19658 (fix)
    Fix bug in svn diff -rN: local propchanges are not shown for
    a directory if we are also reporting remote propchanges for a
    different property on the same directory.
    Justification:
      Localised change; last piece of the diff rework puzzle for 1.4.x.
    Votes:
      +1: malcolm, lundblad

  * r19675
    Fix bug in svn log file@BASE.
    Justification:
      Small change, TortoiseSVN needs the fix.  Regression.
    Votes:
      +1: rooneg, lundblad

Approved changes:

  * r19543
    Fix the convert bug which is caused when converted target is NULL.
    Justification:
      The convert bug raises unnecessary exceptions.
    Votes:
      +1: kou
      +0: nori
